Charter by friar Finlay of Albany, Vicar-Greneral of the order of Friars Preachers in the kingdom of scotland, and guardian of the convent of the house of the Friars Preachers of Ayr, with consent of the said convent, in favour of Sir Henry Stephenson‚ chaplain‚ of a piece of land lying within the walls and precincts of the convent of Ayr, closely adjoining the cemetery of the friars, beginning outwards‚ from the corner of the garden of the said Sir Henry‚ going down by the side of the said cemetery as far as to the Water of Ayr, on the one side, and a piece of land of the said Sir Henry‚ on the other side: To be held in liferent, from the granter and his successom, in fee and heritage, and to revert to the convent simpliciter, after the decease of the grantee. Dated at Ayr 30th August 1409.
